This paper deals with the design and implementation of efficient concurrent data structures, which is a core topic in computer science. The paper also discusses the use of Software Transactional Memory (STM) and smart contracts, which are relevant to distributed systems and cryptography. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.PL (Programming Languages), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.SE (Software Engineering).
